column5: I was up in Minden on Friday for a few hours doing a little GPS-ing for the township as part of a class for school. Anyway, we stopped at Herrington park, just off Horseshoe lake road, and the water was high and flowing fast. I thought i'd share a few photo's and a video with you guys.  -R-

Some very nice shots there, love the whole symbiotical aspect of the water flowing over and around the roots, very cool.  Its a beautiful area, I spent a summer up there working on a project and thoroughly enjoyed it. Thanks.
Now that brings back memories Rambleon.  That river is right by my grandparents old cottage.  When we were kids, we used to go there and collect Mica  Joey
Time to frame some of thoes pics  thanks for shareing
